# Backend (Kotlin + Spring Boot)

## Toolchain

- Kotlin 2.x, JDK 21 LTS, Spring Boot 4.x (WebMVC), Gradle Kotlin DSL with a version catalog. Add `kotlin("plugin.jpa")` only when JPA is actually used. Boot 4 modularized auto-config + test slices: migrations need `spring-boot-starter-flyway`, `@WebMvcTest` needs `spring-boot-starter-webmvc-test`, and the auto-configured `ObjectMapper` is Jackson 3 (`tools.jackson`) — see `context/decisions.md` #50/#51/#52/#53.

## Idioms

- Prefer `data class`, immutability (`val`), and sealed hierarchies. No `!!`. For expected failures use a sealed `Result`/`Outcome` over throwing.
- Constructor injection only — never field injection. Logging via slf4j (`LoggerFactory.getLogger(...)`), never `println`.
- Coroutines: structured concurrency; never `GlobalScope`.

## Layout

- Standard layered packages: `controller/`, `service/`, `domain/`, `repository/`, `config/`. Tests in `src/test/kotlin` mirroring the main package.

## API

- REST under a versioned base path (`/api/v1`). DTOs are separate from entities; validate inputs with Bean Validation. Centralize errors in a `@ControllerAdvice` returning RFC-7807 problem+json.

## Persistence & multilingual data

- Spring Data JPA over PostgreSQL; schema changes via Flyway migrations (never auto `ddl-auto: update` outside dev).
- Tea names are locale-aware (ru/en/zh) — model them as structured localized fields/rows from the start; never assume a single name. Index the searchable locales.

## Tea-database integration

- Wrap each external tea database behind its own client interface; mirror/cache results locally. Rate-limit and retry with backoff. Record each source's name, URL, and license in `context/`.

## Testing

- JUnit5 + MockK; Testcontainers (PostgreSQL) for integration; slice tests (`@WebMvcTest`, `@DataJpaTest`) over full `@SpringBootTest` where possible.

## Don't

- No Lombok (use Kotlin features). No secrets in code or `application.yml` — source them from env / a secret manager.
- No business logic in controllers; no N+1 queries (use fetch joins / entity graphs).
